in the history of Hollywood, from silent films to the digital age, and each is written by an expert in that period. Together, the book’s contributors are able to explore a remarkable range of past and present film industry practices, from the hiring of elocution coaches to the marketing of soundtrack records. Not only does the collection highlight the achievements of renowned sound designers and film composers like Ben Burtt and John Williams, it also honors the unsung workers whose inventions, artistry, and performances have shaped the soundscapes of many notable movies. After you read Sound, you’ll never see—or hear—movies in quite the same way. Sound is a volume in the Behind the Silver Screen series—other titles in the series include Acting; Animation; Art Direction and Production Design; Cinematography; Costume, Makeup, and Hair; Directing; Editing and Special Visual Effects; Producing; and Screenwriting.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 03. Jan 2023) 0aDialogue in motion pictures. 0aMotion picture music. 0aMotion picturesxProduction and direction. 0aMotion picturesxSound effects. 0aSound in motion pictures. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh1 aAment, Vanessa Theme, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeck, Jay, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKalinak, Kathryn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKalinak, Kathryn, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKerins, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPlatte, Nathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSherry, Joseph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSmith, Jeff, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTheme Ament, Vane